Honduras has closed its land, air and maritime borders for the transit of people.
UK special flights
There are currently no further plans for UK-organised special flights from Honduras.
Future travel options
The British Embassy Guatemala City is in contact with airlines, the Honduran authorities and other governments to make sure commercial options for returning to the UK are available as soon as possible.
This travel advice will be updated when departure options become available.
Sign up for email alerts
Registering with the British Embassy
To enable us to respond as quickly as possible to those trying to get home or those affected by COVID-19, please contact us at the following email address: Consular.Honduras@fco.gov.uk.
When doing so, you should provide:
your full name
contact details
location
a brief description of the situation
A member of our consular team will reach out to you as quickly as possible thereafter. If you have already been in direct contact with the consular team, you don’t need to re-send your message.
Your journey home: re-entering the UK
When you return, you must follow the rules for entering the UK. You:
need to provide your journey and contact details up to 48 hours before you’re due to arrive in the UK
are not allowed to leave the place you’re staying for the first 14 days you’re in the UK except in very limited situations (known as ‘self-isolating’)
See also the list of people who are exempt from the border rules.
The National Travel Health Network and Centre (NaTHNaC) also provides advice on how to stay safe as you travel by air.
Help and support
If you need urgent consular assistance, you can contact the British Embassy at consular.Honduras@fco.gov.uk
The Embassy cannot provide further information or advice about departure options over the phone. This page will be updated when departure options become available. To get the latest information, sign up for travel advice email alerts.
If you cannot leave Honduras
If you cannot leave Honduras at this time, see advice on staying in Honduras during coronavirus.
See more information and advice about staying where you are if you cannot return to the UK.
